{"article_id":"c8KDNDAxIC7AIXSx","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Senate Republicans are once again just a few votes away from repealing and replacing Obamacare .","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"It ' s a plan","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"that senators themselves struggle to explain and defend","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"and that emerged on the public stage mere days before an expected vote .","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"How have they found themselves here again ,","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"after their previous repeal bills failed in July ?","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"The underlying truth , the beating heart of Obamacare repeal","depth":13},{"id":7,"text":"that refuses to let it die ,","depth":13},{"id":8,"text":"is :","depth":12},{"id":9,"text":"Republicans just want to pass a bill , any bill ,","depth":13},{"id":10,"text":"to say","depth":14},{"id":11,"text":"they repealed Obamacare .","depth":14},{"id":12,"text":"Whatever standards they ' ve set for their health care plan , whatever promises","depth":13},{"id":13,"text":"they made before , don ' t matter .","depth":13},{"id":14,"text":"The policy is , in a very real sense , beside the point .","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"Republican senators will tell you that themselves , in their own way .","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"\" If we bring this up on the floor ,","depth":14},{"id":17,"text":"I think","depth":15},{"id":18,"text":"every Republican senator is in play","depth":15},{"id":19,"text":"because every Republican senator will be faced with that binary choice , \"","depth":13},{"id":20,"text":"Sen. Ron Johnson","depth":15},{"id":21,"text":"( R-WI ) ,","depth":15},{"id":22,"text":"one of the bill ' s co-sponsors ,","depth":14},{"id":23,"text":"told reporters .","depth":13},{"id":24,"text":"\" Okay , maybe this isn ' t everything they want ,","depth":13},{"id":25,"text":"but the binary choice is :","depth":13},{"id":26,"text":"100 percent guarantee","depth":15},{"id":27,"text":"that Obamacare remains in place ,","depth":15},{"id":28,"text":"and we may have a path to single-payer ,","depth":14},{"id":29,"text":"versus this choice of federalism ,","depth":14},{"id":30,"text":"where we start putting the states back in charge . \"","depth":14},{"id":31,"text":"This bill ,","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"authored by Sens . Lindsey Graham","depth":15},{"id":33,"text":"( R-SC )","depth":15},{"id":34,"text":"and Bill Cassidy","depth":15},{"id":35,"text":"( R-LA ) ,","depth":15},{"id":36,"text":"keeps most of Obamacare ' s taxes","depth":13},{"id":37,"text":"( once a deal breaker for many Republicans ) ,","depth":13},{"id":38,"text":"turns the revenue into a block grant ,","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"and sends the money down to the states with very few strings attached .","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"The block grant looks like nothing from any bill","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"Republicans considered in late July .","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"Several provisions cross what used to be red lines for Republican senators .","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"Graham-Cassidy cuts Medicaid deeply","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"by overhauling the program ' s financing","depth":13},{"id":45,"text":"and ending the Medicaid expansion .","depth":13},{"id":46,"text":"It would allow health insurers to once again charge people higher premiums","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"based on their medical history .","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"The bill should be untenable for other reasons :","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"Graham-Cassidy promises steep spending cuts to most states ,","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"including those","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"represented by Republican senators .","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"It institutes a timeline","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"- states would need to create brand new health care programs by 2020 -","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"that most experts find unreasonable .","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"Yet Senate Republicans could be just a few votes away from passing it .","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"There is only one red line","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"the GOP is really afraid to cross :","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"failing to repeal Obamacare .","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"\" Apparently no one cares what the bill actually does .","depth":13},{"id":60,"text":"That ' s a tough thing to say ,","depth":14},{"id":61,"text":"but it is more true than not ,","depth":14},{"id":62,"text":"\" one Republican lobbyist told me .","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"\" There are so many senators","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"whose public positions in June leave them absolutely no conceivable way","depth":13},{"id":65,"text":"of voting for this . \"","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"If you transport yourself back to the summer ,","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"there were two issues","depth":14},{"id":68,"text":"on which a critical mass of Republican senators were unwilling to bend :","depth":14},{"id":69,"text":"They refused to back deep cuts to Medicaid ,","depth":14},{"id":70,"text":"at least not without a softer landing and a viable alternative","depth":16},{"id":71,"text":"for covering the program ' s current beneficiaries","depth":16},{"id":72,"text":"than the GOP ' s bills provided ;","depth":15},{"id":73,"text":"and they would not roll back Obamacare ' s protections for people with preexisting conditions .","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"Graham-Cassidy ,","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"when you cut through the spin ,","depth":13},{"id":76,"text":"would do both .","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"The bill ends Obamacare ' s Medicaid expansion in 2020 , with no \" glide path \"","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"that Republican senators like Ohio ' s Rob Portman and West Virginia ' s Shelley Moore Capito previously demanded .","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"It ends the expanded eligibility for Medicaid","depth":14},{"id":80,"text":"that Obamacare created ,","depth":14},{"id":81,"text":"and","depth":14},{"id":82,"text":"even if states tried to reconstruct Medicaid expansion on their own with the bill ' s block grant ,","depth":15},{"id":83,"text":"there almost certainly would not be enough money","depth":16},{"id":84,"text":"without an impractical infusion of state dollars .","depth":16},{"id":85,"text":"On top of that , the bill fundamentally overhauls Medicaid","depth":13},{"id":86,"text":"by placing a federal spending cap on the program .","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"The Medicaid spending caps alone would cut the program ' s spending by $ 120 billion , versus current law , by 2026 ,","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"according to Avalere Health , an independent consulting firm .","depth":13},{"id":89,"text":"For much of the debate , those Medicaid cuts and the end of Medicaid expansion were a nonstarter for many Republicans .","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"That ' s what Sen. Dean Heller","depth":15},{"id":91,"text":"( R-NV )","depth":15},{"id":92,"text":"said earlier this year ,","depth":14},{"id":93,"text":"as he stood besides Nevada Gov . Brian Sandoval","depth":13},{"id":94,"text":"and said","depth":14},{"id":95,"text":"he couldn ' t support a bill","depth":15},{"id":96,"text":"that Sandoval opposed .","depth":15},{"id":97,"text":"\" This is all about Medicaid expansion , \"","depth":15},{"id":98,"text":"Heller said ,","depth":15},{"id":99,"text":"adding :","depth":15},{"id":100,"text":"\" It ' s going to be very difficult to get me to a yes . \"","depth":15},{"id":101,"text":"He is now a co-sponsor of Graham-Cassidy ,","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"even though Sandoval opposes it .","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"Sen. Lisa Murkowski","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"( R-AK ) ,","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"one of the most closely watched swing votes","depth":14},{"id":106,"text":"yet to take a public position on Graham-Cassidy ,","depth":14},{"id":107,"text":"suggested to me in June","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"that she couldn ' t support any bill","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"that ended Medicaid expansion .","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"\" I want greater access and lower costs , \"","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"she told me then .","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"\" For instance , if you are going to eliminate Medicaid expansion","depth":13},{"id":113,"text":"or even if you 're going to wind down Medicaid expansion ,","depth":13},{"id":114,"text":"that 's not increasing access . \"","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"As for preexisting conditions , Graham-Cassidy falls short of Republican promises on that issue as well .","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"If states choose to allow it ,","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"insurers could once again charge people higher premiums","depth":14},{"id":118,"text":"based on their medical history , a practice","depth":14},{"id":119,"text":"Obamacare had outlawed .","depth":13},{"id":120,"text":"Cassidy has sought to defend the provision .","depth":13},{"id":121,"text":"\" The protection is the same , \"","depth":14},{"id":122,"text":"he told CNN this week .","depth":14},{"id":123,"text":"His justification is that the bill requires states ,","depth":13},{"id":124,"text":"if they seek a waiver from the Obamacare regulation ,","depth":14},{"id":125,"text":"to describe how they would maintain \" adequate and affordable \" coverage for people adversely affected by the change .","depth":14},{"id":126,"text":"The problem is ,","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"as ' s Sarah Kliff already documented ,","depth":13},{"id":128,"text":"that the bill isn ' t really specific about what those standards actually mean .","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"So it does introduce a degree of uncertainty","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"around how well people with preexisting conditions are protected","depth":13},{"id":131,"text":"that the current health care law does not .","depth":13},{"id":132,"text":"`` You could stretch the definition pretty broadly of what counts , ''","depth":12},{"id":133,"text":"Chris Sloan ,","depth":14},{"id":134,"text":"who has reviewed Graham-Cassidy for Avalere ,","depth":14},{"id":135,"text":"told Kliff .","depth":13},{"id":136,"text":"`` Maybe you fund a high-risk pool","depth":14},{"id":137,"text":"that only allows in some number of people ,","depth":14},{"id":138,"text":"and that counts .","depth":13},{"id":139,"text":"It 's a pretty wide space . ''","depth":12},{"id":140,"text":"Here , again , Republican senators had long pledged","depth":11},{"id":141,"text":"they wouldn ' t touch the protections for preexisting conditions .","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"\" We 're not going to do anything","depth":14},{"id":143,"text":"to change the current law","depth":15},{"id":144,"text":"when it comes to pre-existing conditions ,","depth":15},{"id":145,"text":"I know","depth":14},{"id":146,"text":"which was a big concern with the House bill , \"","depth":14},{"id":147,"text":"Sen. John Cornyn , the No . 2 Republican , said this summer ,","depth":13},{"id":148,"text":"per the Hill .","depth":13},{"id":149,"text":"That position was supposed to be prevalent throughout the Republican conference .","depth":12},{"id":150,"text":"`` I think","depth":15},{"id":151,"text":"people understand","depth":16},{"id":152,"text":"that 's got to be protected ,","depth":16},{"id":153,"text":"and people understand","depth":16},{"id":154,"text":"what happened","depth":17},{"id":155,"text":"when the House dealt with it","depth":18},{"id":156,"text":"and opened it up ,","depth":18},{"id":157,"text":"and it 's just not something","depth":16},{"id":158,"text":"that senators are wishing to do , \"","depth":16},{"id":159,"text":"Sen. Bob Corker","depth":15},{"id":160,"text":"( R-TN )","depth":15},{"id":161,"text":"said a few months ago .","depth":14},{"id":162,"text":"Axios ' s Sam Baker flagged some other provisions","depth":11},{"id":163,"text":"- notably , additional funding","depth":12},{"id":164,"text":"to address the opioid crisis -","depth":12},{"id":165,"text":"that senators had previously conditioned their support on","depth":11},{"id":166,"text":"but aren ' t included in Graham-Cassidy .","depth":11},{"id":167,"text":"Lastly , there were the process complaints .","depth":8},{"id":168,"text":"No Senate health care bill has gone through the regular order of committee hearings , expert testimony , or markups .","depth":9},{"id":169,"text":"The Finance Committee hastily scheduled a hearing for next week ,","depth":11},{"id":170,"text":"but it was a naked attempt","depth":13},{"id":171,"text":"to assuage those concerns from a few key senators","depth":13},{"id":172,"text":"rather than an earnest start to the normal legislative process .","depth":12},{"id":173,"text":"The most prominent critic of the process , Sen. John McCain","depth":14},{"id":174,"text":"( R-AZ ) ,","depth":14},{"id":175,"text":"who has urged Republicans to return to regular order","depth":14},{"id":176,"text":"since he helped sink Obamacare repeal in July ,","depth":14},{"id":177,"text":"seemed to see through the gambit .","depth":12},{"id":178,"text":"Asked if GOP holding 1 hearing addressed his concerns about regular order ,","depth":13},{"id":179,"text":"McCain snapped :","depth":13},{"id":180,"text":"`` Does that sound like regular order to you ? ''","depth":12},{"id":181,"text":"https : //t.co/tPJksFO","depth":7},{"id":182,"text":"9PM - Lindsay Wise","depth":8},{"id":183,"text":"( @ lindsaywise )","depth":8},{"id":184,"text":"September 19 , 2017","depth":7},{"id":185,"text":"The nonpartisan Congressional Budget Office has said","depth":5},{"id":186,"text":"it will be unlikely to provide estimates","depth":7},{"id":187,"text":"on how many people would have health coverage under the bill or what would happen to premiums ,","depth":7},{"id":188,"text":"because of the tight timeline .","depth":6},{"id":189,"text":"Johnson ,","depth":6},{"id":190,"text":"who was at one time fixated on having enough information","depth":7},{"id":191,"text":"to determine his vote ,","depth":7},{"id":192,"text":"dismissed the CBO analysis as \" a detail . \"","depth":5},{"id":193,"text":"Nevertheless ,","depth":4},{"id":194,"text":"despite all those broken promises ,","depth":5},{"id":195,"text":"Senate Republicans are pushing ahead","depth":6},{"id":196,"text":"and might be within just a few votes of passing an Obamacare repeal bill .","depth":7},{"id":197,"text":"It doesn ' t matter which bill it is .","depth":7},{"id":198,"text":"I asked an aide to one Republican senator this week","depth":5},{"id":199,"text":"whether senators actually liked Graham-Cassidy","depth":6},{"id":200,"text":"or whether it was simply the last train","depth":7},{"id":201,"text":"leaving the Obamacare repeal station .","depth":7},{"id":202,"text":"Republicans will be remarkably transparent about this ,","depth":6},{"id":203,"text":"if you ask them .","depth":6},{"id":204,"text":"\" This is not the best possible bill","depth":8},{"id":205,"text":"- this is the best bill possible under the circumstances , \"","depth":8},{"id":206,"text":"Sen. Pat Roberts","depth":9},{"id":207,"text":"( R-KS )","depth":9},{"id":208,"text":"told ' s Jeff Stein .","depth":8},{"id":209,"text":"\" Look ,","depth":9},{"id":210,"text":"we ' re in the back seat of a convertible","depth":11},{"id":211,"text":"being driven by Thelma and Louise ,","depth":11},{"id":212,"text":"and we ' re headed toward the canyon . ...","depth":10},{"id":213,"text":"So we have to get out of the car ,","depth":8},{"id":214,"text":"and you have to have a car","depth":9},{"id":215,"text":"to get into ,","depth":9},{"id":216,"text":"and this is the only car","depth":9},{"id":217,"text":"there is . \"","depth":9},{"id":218,"text":"\" You know ,","depth":7},{"id":219,"text":"I could maybe give you 10 reasons","depth":8},{"id":220,"text":"why this bill shouldn ' t be considered , \"","depth":8},{"id":221,"text":"he told local reporters this week .","depth":6},{"id":222,"text":"\" But Republicans campaigned on this so often","depth":6},{"id":223,"text":"that you have a responsibility","depth":8},{"id":224,"text":"to carry out what you said in the campaign .","depth":8},{"id":225,"text":"That ' s pretty much as much of a reason as the substance of the bill . \"","depth":7},{"id":226,"text":"So","depth":6},{"id":227,"text":"when you cut through the salesmanship around state flexibility and the evils of Obamacare ,","depth":7},{"id":228,"text":"Senate Republicans will tell you right to your face why Graham-Cassidy , a bill","depth":9},{"id":229,"text":"nobody had taken seriously until a week ago ,","depth":9},{"id":230,"text":"might very well pass the chamber in the next few days .","depth":8},{"id":231,"text":"They promised to repeal Obamacare ,","depth":6},{"id":232,"text":"and this is the only Obamacare repeal bill left .","depth":6},{"id":233,"text":"Such an abdication of any coherent policy vision has other Republicans in Washington , particularly those well studied in health policy ,","depth":5},{"id":234,"text":"baffled .","depth":5},{"id":235,"text":"\" I think","depth":7},{"id":236,"text":"this process with Graham-Cassidy is an embarrassment on top of the previous embarrassments","depth":8},{"id":237,"text":"- the cherry on top ,","depth":9},{"id":238,"text":"if you will , \"","depth":9},{"id":239,"text":"a second GOP health care lobbyist told me .","depth":6},{"id":240,"text":"\" A sweeping revision of federal-state roles in and funding arrangements for health care , with one hearing , no markups , no CBO score .","depth":6},{"id":241,"text":"Good grief . \"","depth":6},{"id":242,"text":"\" I still believe","depth":5},{"id":243,"text":"conservatives and Republicans have strong ideas","depth":6},{"id":244,"text":"for improving how health care is financed and delivered , \"","depth":6},{"id":245,"text":"the lobbyist continued .","depth":4},{"id":246,"text":"\" But will anyone listen to them","depth":4},{"id":247,"text":"after this debacle is finally and mercifully over ? \"","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":495,"left":465,"right":494,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":465,"left":440,"right":464,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":440,"left":432,"right":439,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":432,"left":253,"right":431,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":253,"left":251,"right":252,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":251,"left":0,"right":250,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":250,"left":1,"right":249,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":249,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":252,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":431,"left":413,"right":430,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":413,"left":302,"right":412,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":302,"left":294,"right":301,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":294,"left":277,"right":293,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":277,"left":261,"right":276,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":261,"left":260,"right":14,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":260,"left":255,"right":259,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":255,"left":254,"right":8,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":254,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":259,"left":257,"right":258,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":257,"left":9,"right":256,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":256,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":258,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":276,"left":15,"right":275,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":275,"left":268,"right":274,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":268,"left":264,"right":267,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":264,"left":263,"right":19,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":263,"left":16,"